Tom -

The &#39;check&#39; script is run whenever the &#39;cttmp&#39; script fails, to see if 
the problem is with the Cantera installation.  Unfortunately the 
single-line &#39;check&#39; script will always fail, since it tries to import 
module &#39;ctml_writer&#39; from the Cantera package  (where it used to be), 
instead of importing it directly.  The workaround is to copy file 
&#39;ctml_writer.py&#39; from the &#39;site_packages&#39; folder in the Python Library 
folder to the &#39;Cantera&#39; folder within &#39;site_packages&#39;.   it seems to me 
now that running the &#39;check&#39; script is more trouble than it is worth, 
and I am removing this step from the procedure followed to translate 
input files.

But this does not answer why the cttmp script fails, since it works 
when you run it from the command line.  I&#39;m not sure why that is 
happening, but it must be some sort of path problem.  Perhaps try the 
above fix and try again and see what happens...

By the way - I assume you are using WinXP or Win2000.  Cantera will 
encounter problems under Win98 or WinME.

Dave


